================================================================================
Attribution for upstream and reference projects
================================================================================

htmlwasher is a TypeScript port of Trafilatura. The projects below fall into two
kinds: those htmlwasher is DERIVED FROM (their code is ported or copied and ships
in this package — attribution required by their licenses), and those CONSULTED as
design/idiom references (no code shipped — credited as a courtesy). Each entry
states which. The text of the Apache License, Version 2.0 referenced below is
reproduced in this repository's LICENSE file.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Trafilatura (the canonical original) — Apache-2.0
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Author:  Adrien Barbaresi
Source:  https://github.com/adbar/trafilatura
Docs:    https://trafilatura.readthedocs.io/

DERIVED FROM (attribution required). The canonical original. htmlwasher's metadata
subsystem (src/metadata/*) is a direct port of its Python (metadata.py,
json_metadata.py, utils.py, xpaths.py) — the AUTHOR_* and METANAME_* tables are
copied verbatim and the transforms transcribed — and htmlwasher follows its overall
extraction semantics, option behavior, and test corpus. (Trafilatura was GPLv3+
before v1.8.0, then relicensed to Apache-2.0; htmlwasher ports the Apache-2.0 codebase.)

Citation:
  Barbaresi, A. (2021). "Trafilatura: A Web Scraping Library and Command-Line
  Tool for Text Discovery and Extraction." Proceedings of the Joint Conference
  of the 59th Annual Meeting of the Association for Computational Linguistics
  and the 11th International Joint Conference on Natural Language Processing:
  System Demonstrations, 122-131. https://aclanthology.org/2021.acl-demo.15/

