rs-trafilatura and web-page-classifier — MIT OR Apache-2.0 (used under Apache-2.0)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Author:  Murrough Foley
Sources: https://github.com/Murrough-Foley/rs-trafilatura
         https://github.com/Murrough-Foley/web-page-classifier

rs-trafilatura — DERIVED FROM (attribution required). htmlwasher's page-type-aware
layer is derived from it: the URL-pattern tables (page_type/mod.rs), the 7 per-type
extraction profiles and selector tables, the HTML-signal refinement, the
is_boilerplate guards, and the 89 numeric classifier features are copied/transcribed
into src/classifier/*, src/profiles/*, and src/core/*.

web-page-classifier — CONSULTED (courtesy). Referenced for the page-type feature set
and XGBoost classifier design; htmlwasher's classifier is independently implemented
and its model is trained fresh from WCXB, so no web-page-classifier code ships.

Both are dual-licensed MIT OR Apache-2.0; used here under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

