Bundled npm dependencies — permissive (MIT / ISC)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
htmlwasher's HTML-washing pillar and DOM/inference layers are built on the
following open-source libraries, used under their respective permissive licenses.

Runtime (always installed):
  sanitize-html         — the default HTML sanitizer (the washing levels). MIT.
  parse5                — WHATWG-compliant HTML normalization. MIT.
  linkedom              — the primary DOM. ISC.
  htmlparser2           — fast HTML parsing. MIT.
  prettier              — HTML pretty-printing. MIT.
  html-minifier-terser  — HTML minification (bundles terser, BSD-2-Clause). MIT.
  chardet, iconv-lite   — byte→string decoding. MIT.
  commander             — CLI argument parsing. MIT.
  onnxruntime-node      — default ONNX inference for the page-type classifier. MIT.

Optional (installed only if the consumer opts into the hardened or web backend):
  dompurify             — opt-in "hardened" sanitizer backend.
                          MPL-2.0 OR Apache-2.0 (used under Apache-2.0).
  jsdom                 — DOM for the hardened backend. MIT.
  onnxruntime-web       — WASM/web ONNX inference backend. MIT.

These are dependencies, not vendored source; their full license texts ship in
their respective npm packages under node_modules, so a plain `npm install` of
htmlwasher already carries each notice. If you instead redistribute a bundled or
vendored build that inlines these, reproduce their MIT/ISC/BSD/Apache notices.
